  <section xml:id="customizing-images-and-product-images-downloading">
    <title>Downloading files for image customization</title>
    <para>
      To get the necessary files that define the custom image, proceed as follows:
    </para>
    <procedure>
      <step>
        <para>
Navigate to the <link xlink:href="https://build.opensuse.org/project/show/SUSE:SLFO:Products:SL-Micro:6.2">&osuse; build service</link>.
        </para>
      </step>
      <step>
        <para>
          Download the package <literal>SL-Micro</literal>.
        </para>
      </step>
    </procedure>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="customizing-images-and-product-images-modifications">
    <title>Modifying image definitions files</title>
    <para>
      After you have downloaded the <literal>SL-Micro</literal> package, unpack it. The file
      <filename>SL-Micro.kiwi</filename> is the main configuration file that you can modify. The
      files defines the following items: 
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          the type of image to be built. For details, refer to the <link
          xlink:href="https://doc.opensuse.org/projects/kiwi/doc/#sec.description.preferences"><literal>preferences</literal>
          definition</link>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          repositories to use either the &suse; open build service ones or your custom
          repositories. Fore details, refer to the <link
          xlink:href="https://doc.opensuse.org/projects/kiwi/doc/#sec.description.repository"><literal>repository</literal>
          definition</link>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          RPM packages to install. For details, refer to the <link
          xlink:href="https://doc.opensuse.org/projects/kiwi/doc/#sec.description.packages"><literal>packages</literal>
          definition</link>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          scripts to run during the build process. For details, refer to the <link xlink:href="https://doc.opensuse.org/projects/kiwi/doc/#sec.hooks">boot image hook-scripts</link>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          custom configuration. For details, refer to <xref linkend="customizing-images-and-product-images-custom-config"/>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  
  <section xml:id="customizing-images-and-product-images-custom-config">
    <title>Adding custom files</title>
    <para>
You can add your custom configuration files to the image. To do so, proceed as follows:
    </para>
    <procedure>
      <step>
        <para>
Create a directory <filename>root</filename> in the same directory as is your <filename>SL-Micro.kiwi</filename>.
        </para>
      </step>
      <step>
        <para>
          Inside <filename>root</filename>, create the directory path where you want your file to be placed.
        </para>
      </step>
      <step>
        <para>
          Put your custom configuration file in that directory.
        </para>
      </step>
    </procedure>
    <para>
      Alternatively, to generate the files during the image build process, use the
      <filename>config.sh</filename> scipt. For details, refer to the <link
      xlink:href="https://osinside.github.io/kiwi/concept_and_workflow/shell_scripts.html">KIWI
      documentation</link>.
    </para>
    
  </section>
  </section>

